---
import DocsLayout from "../../layouts/DocsLayout.astro";
import { SITE } from "../../config";
---

<DocsLayout
  title="Troubleshooting · Squeezy"
  description="How to debug Squeezy startup, provider, graph, permission, and report issues."
  activeDoc="/docs/troubleshooting/"
  eyebrow="support"
  heading="Start with local evidence."
  lead="The support path mirrors the product architecture: inspect local config, run diagnostics, ask Squeezy local help, then prepare a redacted report when maintainers need more detail."
>
  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>First commands</h2>
    <div class="doc-card-grid">
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">doctor</span>
        <h3>Environment check</h3>
        <pre><code>squeezy doctor</code></pre>
        <p>Checks config sources, repo profile, provider credential, session store, and sandbox availability.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="card">
        <span class="label">config</span>
        <h3>Effective settings</h3>
        <pre><code>squeezy config inspect</code></pre>
        <p>Shows merged settings with sensitive values redacted.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Ask Squeezy how Squeezy works</h2>
    <p>Use `/help`, `/help providers`, `/help sessions`, `/help permissions`, or a natural question about Squeezy. Product-help questions are answered from bundled docs and redacted config before provider work starts, so Squeezy can explain its own setup without spending model tokens first.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Unexpected permissions</h2>
    <p>Inspect `[permissions]`, `[[permissions.rules]]`, and `[permissions.shell_sandbox]` in `squeezy config inspect`. With no overrides, default mode allows workspace read/search/edit plus local shell, git, and compiler commands; web, MCP, destructive actions, and outside-workspace file paths still ask.</p>
    <p>Default and auto-review modes use `network = "allow_when_approved"` unless the shell sandbox network policy is explicitly configured. Set `network = "deny_by_default"` when approved network-classified shell commands should still run without network access.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="doc-block">
    <h2>Report an issue</h2>
    <pre><code>/feedback
/report
squeezy sessions report &lt;session_id&gt; --preview
squeezy sessions report &lt;session_id&gt; --send</code></pre>
    <p>Feedback is short redacted text. Reports are redacted diagnostic archives with a preview step. Public GitHub issues should include a sanitized summary and returned feedback/report id, not private code or archive contents.</p>
    <div class="actions">
      <a class="button" href={SITE.issuesUrl} data-track-click="troubleshooting_issues" data-track-target="github">Open GitHub issues</a>
    </div>
  </section>
</DocsLayout>
